g.title: j1716377664
g.text: I think you left a fancy energy-blasting pistol thing here

g.title: j4152201484
g.text: Um, no. All my "fancy energy-blasting pistol things" are accounted for.

g.title: j83404341
g.text: enh, I guess I'll just leave it

g.title: j2727031404
g.text: You seem upset. Is it something I said?

g.title: j3168902935
g.text: should I ask u about the weather?

g.title: j4023617339
g.text: I didn't love being called boring.

g.title: j254983825
g.text: then I guess that's all for now!

g.title: j3677036242
g.text: Oh. I really didn't mean anything by it.

g.title: j3898030034
g.text: Depends on what the coolant towers are up to

g.title: j898428929
g.text: I'd have to check. Either kind of cold or super cold. Either way, cold.

g.title: j4087849636
g.text: Honest. I'm sorry I upset you.

g.title: j2592337470
g.text: You're not boring, Aoi. I just thought I was being clever.

g.title: j3866043639
g.text: If you were really boring, I wouldn't be talking to you.

g.title: j3869558825
g.text: It seems the jury's convinced by your defense

g.title: j3707488228
g.text: I was joking. I thought venus couldn't sustain life lol

g.title: j6653911
g.text: and grants you a fresh start

g.title: j1829801149
g.text: Oh yeah. I guess you're in the time when Venus was inhospitable... Wild.

g.title: j3538319091
g.text: Ah right. In the future, the Orokin come along and invent coolant towers that cool Venus down.

g.title: j377657138
g.text: Oh, I see Aoi's emoticons are back. I think that's a good sign.

g.title: j2228668588
g.text: I'll do you one better. These days, people with robotic body upgrades maintain the towers, and I get along great with them.

g.title: j3337659708
g.text: Not at all. I go there all the time. We created planet-cooling technology ages ago. Lol.

g.title: j3396606781
g.text: cool! did we fix jupiter too?

g.title: j4268120866
g.text: There's only so much one can do with a gas giant, but there are stations in its atmosphere.

g.title: j1422949882
g.text: Well, what do you mean by "fix"? But not really.

g.title: j2538410231
g.text: darn. I guess I'll live with that midnight mind-trap forever.

g.title: j3208607950
g.text: I'd be happy to help free you of that mind-trap if I can.

g.title: j2687130506
g.text: Lettie told me if u fell into jupiter, u'd hit a point where the atmosphere is denser than ur body, so u'd bob up and down. stuck. forever falling then getting launched back up between densities

g.title: j2649864430
g.text: u know when ur mind settles into the quiet of the night and starts pulling all kinds of crazy things from your subconscious as u try to sleep? mind-traps!

g.title: j3561771688
g.text: Oh. Hah. Yeah, I know what you mean. You have one about Jupiter?

g.title: j865309876
g.text: I have no idea what you're talking about.

g.title: j2047949676
g.text: that is until u disintegrate! plus it's the size of like 1300 earths... long fall... long launch!

g.title: j2101086065
g.text: Not that I'm judging. What's this Jupiter-related "mind-trap"?

g.title: j1248208449
g.text: You'd die quickly anyway. Just your body would be floating there, not "you" exactly.

g.title: j2517703825
g.text: I don't know if this helps, but size is relative. Earth actually seems pretty small when you live in space.

g.title: j3269032543
g.text: gosh no! It's not like that. It's just... wow this is embarrassing heh

g.title: j4074039097
g.text: and it always will be! but it helps to talk about it :')

g.title: j3693179539
g.text: not super comforting, but I appreciate the effort

g.title: j4260418839
g.text: it's not like I'm an astronaut anyway

g.title: j3046305165
g.text: jupiter would be a nightmare even if it were the size of earth tho

g.title: j4083358295
g.text: Hang on, I didn't mean to embarrass you. Sorry. Maybe I misunderstood.

g.title: j893428279
g.text: ^_^ it was just a roundabout way of saying I'm kinda scared of jupiter

g.title: j4215598385
g.text: oh duh! I guess u wouldn't have astronauts anymore

g.title: j3806244323
g.text: which I guess sounds silly to a future-person who hangs out in its atmosphere like all the time...

g.title: j1269293083
g.text: the word's kinda meaningless when EVERYONE's an astronaut lol

g.title: j1609199609
g.text: Not at all. Tell me more. :)

g.title: j2002910543
g.text: So an astronaut is someone who lives in space?

g.title: j4004242132
g.text: I still have no idea what you're talking about.

g.title: j1618414117
g.text: an astronaut is someone who *explores* space. people can't live there yet, but we visit!

g.title: j1566528044
g.text: That's pretty exciting. Humans are on the cusp of discovering so much, and you get to be right there to see it.

g.title: j260282747
g.text: What's it like to be talking to a real live astronaut?

g.title: j3145270366
g.text: :) that's a really cool way to look at it

g.title: j29093123
g.text: ummm... I've been enjoying our convo so much that I ignored the fancy energy-blasting pistol thing leaking some kinda green ooze onto the floor...

g.title: j2953449321
g.text: it's starting to smell weird sooo

g.title: j41114900
g.text: I'm gonna get Quincy to deal with that
